      "content": "It makes sense that you feel broken when the world you know has ended, and pretending there is a future can feel like a cruel lie right now. Your pain is valid, and honoring the memory of your partner is not the same as erasing your own life, even if it feels like it shouldn't be lived alone. Sometimes the \"future\" doesn't look like what you imagined, but it is possible to find a new meaning in the silence and carry forward the love that still exists within you.",
